Title: Taking A $15 Casio F91W 5,000 Meters Underwater
Description: Brands like Rolex and Omega will often tout their deepsea capabilities with the Rolex Deepsea Challenge rated to 11,000 meters (36,090 feet) and the Omega Ultra Deep coming in at a lesser but still ridiculous 6,000 meters (20,000 feet) of theoretical water resistance. But what about a cheap Casio often associated with terrorists and hipsters? With around $15 and some engineering know-how, can an affordable watch also venture into the deep ocean?

Title: No-Tracking Queries: Speed Up Your EF Core Like a Pro - Chris Woody Woodruff
Description: Imagine you‚Äôre at a library, flipping through books at lightning speed. You don‚Äôt need to write notes in the margins or keep tabs on which books you‚Äôve touched‚Äîyou‚Äôre just reading. That‚Äôs what no-tracking queries are in EF Core: a way to grab data without keeping track of changes. It‚Äôs fast, lightweight, and perfect for read-only operations. But wait, there‚Äôs more! Let‚Äôs throw identity resolution into the mix, a smart way to avoid duplicate entities when working with no-tracking queries. Together, they make a dynamic duo for blazing-fast data fetching, significantly reducing the time it takes to retrieve data from the database.

Title: Scaling Webhooks with Message Queues. Fix Your Bottlenecks (part 4)
Description:
Want to master Clean Architecture? Go here: https://bit.ly/3PupkOJ
Want to unlock Modular Monoliths? Go here: https://bit.ly/3SXlzSt
Get the source code here: https://www.patreon.com/milanjovanovic

Struggling with webhook performance? In this video, we'll tackle one of the biggest challenges in modern web applications: scaling webhook processing. I'll show you how to identify and fix common bottlenecks using RabbitMQ and MassTransit, transforming your webhook architecture from a potential system bottleneck into a robust, scalable solution. We'll start by demonstrating common webhook problems, then dive deep into implementing a message queue-based solution with RabbitMQ, and finally explore how to properly structure your application using MassTransit for reliable message processing. Whether you're handling dozens or thousands of webhook events, this step-by-step guide will show you the industry-standard approach to building a production-ready webhook system.
